      <akn:section eId="sec_24_923">
        <akn:num>24-923</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Location of BOOT CAMP.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_24-923_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Director shall use an existing building or set of buildings, which may be located in the Washington Metropolitan area, to establish a residential center for the BOOT CAMP participants.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_24-923_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The residential center shall include classrooms, a counseling and vocational training center, separate sleeping accommodations for male and female participants, a dining facility, outdoor drill and recreation areas, and other usages that are necessary for the efficient operation of the BOOT CAMP.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
